Section 1: Hands-on Task (Docker Run)
Command:
docker run -d -p 8080:80 nginx
Questions
1. What does -d do?
2. What does -p 8080:80 mean internally?
3. Where is nginx actually running? Host or container?
4. Why can multiple nginx containers run on the same machine?

Solutions:- 

1. -d (Detached Mode)
Runs container in background
Frees terminal immediately
Without -d, container runs in attached mode

2. -p 8080:80 (Port Mapping)

Maps:

Host (8080) → Container (80)
🔍 Internal Flow:
Browser → localhost:8080
        ↓
Host Network Stack
        ↓
iptables NAT rule (Docker)
        ↓
Docker Bridge Network
        ↓
Container (port 80)

3. Where nginx runs?
Inside container
But container = isolated process on host kernel (not VM)

4. Multiple Containers
Because of:

Namespaces → isolation
cgroups → resource control
Shared kernel → lightweight
